bug.short_desc: Problem when export the attached report design with different format.

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86079 report design
There're several problem when export the attached report design.
build version: 2.3.0 v20070103-0800
steps to reproduce: 1. Download the attached report design. 2. Preview the design file with web viewer. 3. Click the export report button. 4. Export report in Excel/Postscript/PDF/Powerpoint.
Expected result: The report can be exported in different format correctly.
Actual result: When export in excel format, problem occurs. See attachment:excel.
When export in Postscript/PDF, some text are clipped.
When export in Powerpoint, some text are displayed in the space between two pages.

When exporting a report, the default option is set to "Actual size". 1) PPT: a ppt page does not have CLIP, so contents spread out 2) PDF/PS: contents are clipped
If set the option to "Fit to wholepage", PPT, PDF and PS all get the right result. So these are the right behavior.
For Excel, the problem is caused by wrong bookmarks, like misproper characters.

We use Excel range names to build bookmarks in excel output. So if the user defined bookmarks do not obey the range name constraints, the whole generated excel file can not be opened.
Currently, our solution is 1. check if the bookmark is valid for excel. 2. if so, write it into excel file. 3. if not, log the "Invalid bookmark name for Excel!" warning and ignore the bookmark.
verified on build 2.3.0 v20080205-0800 and closed.
